1
00:00:19,894 --> 00:00:24,315
♪ <i>I was walking along,
minding my business</i> ♪

2
00:00:24,398 --> 00:00:27,610
♪ <i>When out of an orange colored sky</i> ♪

3
00:00:27,693 --> 00:00:31,572
♪ <i>Flash, bam, alakazam</i> ♪

4
00:00:31,656 --> 00:00:34,534
♪ <i>Wonderful you came by</i> ♪

5
00:00:35,034 --> 00:00:38,955
♪ <i>I was humming a tune
Drinking in sunshine</i> ♪

6
00:00:39,038 --> 00:00:42,208
♪ <i>When out of that orange colored view</i> ♪

7
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:45,503
♪ <i>Flash, bam, alakazam</i> ♪

8
00:00:45,586 --> 00:00:46,879
♪ <i>I got a look at you...</i> ♪

9
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:51,759
♪ <i>One look and I yelled timber...</i> ♪

10
00:00:51,842 --> 00:00:54,178
<i>Negotiations
were scheduled to continue today</i>

11
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:57,807
<i>As the White House had no comment
about the President's whereabouts.</i>

12
00:01:01,769 --> 00:01:03,271
Ready to be
of service, madam.

13
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:05,523
<i>...between America
and her adversaries</i>

14
00:01:05,606 --> 00:01:08,192
<i>crumbled this morning
in Anchorage, Alaska.</i>

15
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:11,445
<i>The specter of nuclear war
facing this nation</i>

16
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:13,656
<i>For ten long years is final...</i>

17
00:01:14,865 --> 00:01:18,160
It's a party. Let's just focus
on the party, okay?

18
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:22,873
♪ <i>Pretty green polka dot sky</i> ♪

19
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:24,584
♪ <i>Flash, bam...</i> ♪

20
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:27,086
Look at that!

21
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:31,424
Well done!

22
00:01:34,176 --> 00:01:35,761
All right, birthday boy.

23
00:01:36,721 --> 00:01:38,389
Let's get a photo of you
up here on Sugarfoot.

24
00:01:39,098 --> 00:01:42,310
Why the hell is Cooper Howard
working kids' birthday parties?

25
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:45,438
What else? Alimony.

26
00:01:46,522 --> 00:01:47,732
What'd they say, Dad?

27
00:01:49,942 --> 00:01:52,403
That I'm lucky to have
such a good helper like you.

28
00:01:54,655 --> 00:01:55,865
All right, you ready?

29
00:01:58,492 --> 00:01:59,869
-It's good.
-All right, good.

30
00:01:59,952 --> 00:02:01,912
Here we go, bud.

31
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:05,166
Hey, honey. Honey, get with Cooper.
Let's get a picture.

32
00:02:05,249 --> 00:02:07,168
Uh, you bet. Yeah. All right.

33
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:10,713
Oh, Coop, Coop, Coop, do your thumbs-up.

34
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:14,967
Yeah, given the state of everything,
I prefer not to, if that's all right.

35
00:02:15,051 --> 00:02:17,553
Why not? It's what you're famous for.

36
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:18,846
-Drop it, Bob.
-Yeah.

37
00:02:19,347 --> 00:02:21,515
We gotta...
we gotta get this rodeo on the road.

38
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,351
I can't thank you enough, Mr. Howard.

39
00:02:23,434 --> 00:02:26,979
Pleasure's all mine, ma'am.
I hope your son had a lovely birthday.

40
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:28,230
-Perfect.
-Yeah.

41
00:02:28,773 --> 00:02:29,857
Who's ready for cake?

42
00:02:29,940 --> 00:02:31,651
- Me!
- All right. You ready, Janey?

43
00:02:34,028 --> 00:02:36,364
Come on. There you go.

44
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:39,450
-Pinko.
-Yep. He still took my money.

45
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:44,413
♪ <i>Happy birthday, dear Roy</i> ♪

46
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:49,377
♪ <i>Happy birthday to you</i> ♪

47
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,595
<i>Here's that Los Angeles sunshine
coming through.</i>

48
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,597
<i>Hal... I can't... I can't--</i>

49
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:04,308
<i>Sorry, I can't do the weather if I don't
know if there'll be a next week.</i>

50
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:06,268
Only thinking happy thoughts today.

51
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,645
<i>...the Nuka Cola bottle...</i>

52
00:03:08,562 --> 00:03:11,482
<i>Sugar Bombs presents</i> Grognak the Barbarian

53
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:12,983
and the Ruby Ruins

54
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:17,530
<i>And, as I say
this is hi from the past!</i>

55
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:21,409
All right.

56
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:23,202
<i>I'm sick of you.</i>

57
00:03:23,285 --> 00:03:24,829
Think that's everything.

58
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:28,666
Why wouldn't you do it?

59
00:03:28,749 --> 00:03:30,042
The thumbs-up.

60
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:32,712
Oh, it's, uh...

61
00:03:33,295 --> 00:03:35,589
It's grown-up stuff.

62
00:03:41,178 --> 00:03:42,763
Back when I was in the Marines,

63
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:46,267
They taught us that if they ever
dropped a really big bomb,

64
00:03:46,892 --> 00:03:48,978
They told us to hold up your thumb
just like this.

65
00:03:49,687 --> 00:03:52,690
And if the cloud is smaller
than your thumb,

66
00:03:53,482 --> 00:03:54,525
Then you run for the hills.

67
00:03:54,608 --> 00:03:56,569
And if it's bigger than your thumb?

68
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:00,156
They told us not to bother running.

69
00:04:01,365 --> 00:04:03,367
Do you think it's gonna happen?

70
00:04:05,161 --> 00:04:06,454
I certainly hope not.

71
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:10,040
But us cowpokes,
we take it as it comes, right?

72
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,424
Can I have a slice, Dad?

73
00:04:19,216 --> 00:04:23,345
Know what, let me see
if I can't rustle you up a piece.

74
00:04:45,284 --> 00:04:48,621
All right, one piece of cake
coming up for my favorite cowgirl.

75
00:04:49,413 --> 00:04:51,582
Is it your thumb or mine?

76
00:05:15,731 --> 00:05:17,983
That's smoke, Janey. It's just a fire.

77
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:08,951
-Let us in.
-No room.

78
00:06:09,034 --> 00:06:10,578
-Bob...
-Back off!

79
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:11,787
Bob!

80
00:07:13,515 --> 00:07:15,184
My name is Lucy MacLean,

81
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:18,187
And I'm an active contributor
to the well-being of my community.

82
00:07:19,229 --> 00:07:20,272
<i>Repair skills.</i>

83
00:07:20,356 --> 00:07:23,317
<i>I enjoy participating
in the Young Pipefitters' Association,</i>

84
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,444
<i>Which keeps me active.</i>

85
00:07:25,527 --> 00:07:27,112
Science skills.

86
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:29,490
Obviously, minor,
nothing compared to my dad's,

87
00:07:29,573 --> 00:07:32,076
<i>But I always relish a challenge.</i>

88
00:07:32,159 --> 00:07:33,369
<i>Speech skills.</i>

89
00:07:33,452 --> 00:07:36,246
<i>My primary passion
is teaching American history,</i>

90
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:37,623
<i>With a focus on ethics.</i>

91
00:07:37,706 --> 00:07:39,959
<i>I also participate in Gymnastics Club.</i>

92
00:07:41,085 --> 00:07:42,086
<i>Fencing team C.</i>

93
00:07:44,922 --> 00:07:46,382
<i>Intermediate phys-ed.</i>

94
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,343
<i>And I dabble in riflery.</i>

95
00:07:50,552 --> 00:07:52,388
<i>Though, I'm not very good.</i>

96
00:07:54,431 --> 00:07:55,766
<i>In my personal time,</i>

97
00:07:55,849 --> 00:07:58,644
<i>I enjoy taking walks
and watching movies with my dad.</i>

98
00:07:59,186 --> 00:08:01,021
<i>Gardening, also with my dad.</i>

99
00:08:01,105 --> 00:08:03,649
<i>And participating
in my family book club.</i>

100
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:07,069
<i>We're still trying
to get my brother on board.</i>

101
00:08:07,152 --> 00:08:08,737
<i>He'll come around when he's ready.</i>

102
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:13,367
My reproductive organs are intact,
my hygiene, well-maintained.

103
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:17,871
And yet, I have been unable
to find a suitable marriage partner.

104
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:20,416
At least one I'm not related to.

105
00:08:20,499 --> 00:08:22,584
And we have rules about that
for a reason.

106
00:08:24,128 --> 00:08:26,922
So, it is with sound mind and body

107
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:29,466
That I hereby submit
my application to the council

108
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:32,761
To participate in the triennial trade
with Vault 32.

109
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:13,844
Norman.

110
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,458
Feels a little tight.

111
00:09:44,541 --> 00:09:45,542
Won't be for long.

112
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:48,879
On my wedding night, that dress got off
almost as fast as Burt did.

113
00:09:49,838 --> 00:09:50,672
Huh.

114
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:53,675
Oh, gosh.

115
00:09:54,259 --> 00:09:55,594
After ten years of cousin stuff,

116
00:09:55,677 --> 00:09:57,679
I'm definitely excited
for the real thing.

117
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:02,768
Oh, Lucy, I am just excited for us
to raise our kids together.

118
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:53,026
Dad.

119
00:10:54,778 --> 00:10:58,157
My little sugar bomb. Oh.

120
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:01,034
Oh.

121
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:03,871
Gosh, you look just like your mother.

122
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,666
Yeah, I wish she was here.

123
00:11:08,792 --> 00:11:09,793
Me too.

124
00:11:10,919 --> 00:11:11,920
Were you scared...

125
00:11:12,921 --> 00:11:14,256
When you married Mom?

126
00:11:14,339 --> 00:11:15,465
Me?

127
00:11:16,216 --> 00:11:17,843
Terrified.

128
00:11:18,468 --> 00:11:21,680
Well, I'd never stepped foot
outside Vault 31.

129
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:23,599
When did it go away?

130
00:11:24,808 --> 00:11:26,351
The moment I met your mother.

131
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:28,061
Lucy.

132
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:31,273
Lucy.

133
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:38,405
From that moment on,
Vault 31 was a distant memory to me.

134
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:44,661
Overseer. It's time.

135
00:12:08,101 --> 00:12:10,520
Must be nerve-racking.
Your husband could be anybody.

136
00:12:11,396 --> 00:12:12,481
I'm aware.

137
00:12:12,564 --> 00:12:13,857
-As for his looks...
-Who knows?

138
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:17,236
Big butt, no butt.
But that's just a superficial concern.

139
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:19,571
-It's what's on the inside that counts.
-That's right.

140
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:20,989
And in that respect,
he could be a cannibal

141
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:22,366
Or just crammed full of tumors...

142
00:12:22,449 --> 00:12:23,617
Norman!

143
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:24,534
Sorry, Dad.

144
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:39,883
Gatekeeper.

145
00:12:47,349 --> 00:12:48,183
Chet?

146
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:51,228
Honestly... textbook tumbler jam.

147
00:12:51,311 --> 00:12:54,106
It's gonna take some time to fix.

148
00:12:54,189 --> 00:12:56,483
Probably best if we reschedule
with the 32s

149
00:12:56,566 --> 00:12:57,943
-Until maintenance and I can...
-Chet.

150
00:12:59,403 --> 00:13:00,487
What's going on?

151
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,240
Lucy, I love you.

152
00:13:06,493 --> 00:13:07,911
We all know that, Chet.

153
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:10,831
Messing around with your cousin,
it's all well and good for kids,

154
00:13:10,914 --> 00:13:15,210
But it's not a sustainable
long-term sexual practice, you know?

155
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:18,046
Yeah, I know.

156
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,464
Welcome, neighbors from Vault 32.

157
00:14:00,547 --> 00:14:04,176
I am Hank MacLean, Overseer of Vault 33.

158
00:14:05,302 --> 00:14:08,472
Lee Moldaver, Overseer of 32.

159
00:14:09,473 --> 00:14:11,516
Thank you for your hospitality.

160
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:15,187
Oh, we were sorry to hear
of Overseer Jackson's passing

161
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:16,438
In your telegrams.

162
00:14:16,521 --> 00:14:19,900
When blight hit our wheat,
we lost a lot of good people.

163
00:14:19,983 --> 00:14:23,028
But this trade will help us
get back on our feet.

164
00:14:23,111 --> 00:14:28,325
Yes, well, as arranged, we offer you
seed and parts for machinery.

165
00:14:28,408 --> 00:14:30,619
In exchange, we offer you a breeder.

166
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:32,704
So...

167
00:14:33,538 --> 00:14:35,499
Who am I marrying?

168
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:48,345
I'm Lucy.

169
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:49,930
Do you have a name?

170
00:14:50,972 --> 00:14:51,807
Monty.

171
00:14:57,896 --> 00:14:59,272
Lucky.

172
00:15:07,489 --> 00:15:14,079
♪ <i>Who do you suppose I really love...</i> ♪

173
00:15:29,136 --> 00:15:30,720
So, what's your sperm count?

174
00:15:34,933 --> 00:15:35,767
Uh...

175
00:15:36,518 --> 00:15:39,312
Your Vault's doctor must check
every physical, no?

176
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:42,190
I mean, sperm is pretty important
in perpetuating America.

177
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,400
- So...
- Stop.

178
00:15:49,156 --> 00:15:54,161
Good evening and welcome
to the proud denizens of Vault 32.

179
00:16:01,918 --> 00:16:07,466
We are bonded not just as neighbors,

180
00:16:07,549 --> 00:16:09,134
But by a shared duty.

181
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:13,305
To keep the candle of civilization lit

182
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:17,851
While the rest of the world
has been cast into darkness.

183
00:16:19,394 --> 00:16:23,523
Soon, if our measurements are correct,

184
00:16:24,065 --> 00:16:27,611
Radiation levels on the surface
are dropping fast enough

185
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:32,282
That the next generation,
Lucy and Monty's children,

186
00:16:32,365 --> 00:16:35,327
Will be able to recolonize.

187
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:39,289
Yeah!

188
00:16:40,248 --> 00:16:41,249
Yes.

189
00:16:44,294 --> 00:16:46,296
Now, after 200 years...

190
00:16:47,422 --> 00:16:49,299
We don't know much
about what's up there.

191
00:16:50,425 --> 00:16:55,514
Desperation, violence, lawlessness.

192
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:59,976
These survivors will need
to be shown a better way.

193
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:04,147
I'll admit, I'm sometimes afraid

194
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:07,984
That mean old world
will change us instead.

195
00:17:09,110 --> 00:17:10,695
But then I look at my daughter...

196
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:15,367
Such a beautiful bride,
and her new husband...

197
00:17:16,451 --> 00:17:18,537
And I am not afraid.

198
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:21,915
I feel hope.

199
00:17:24,167 --> 00:17:28,338
To Lucy MacLean,
and to this marriage, and to hope.

200
00:17:31,466 --> 00:17:33,635
Let's dance. Ha-ha. Hit it.

201
00:17:33,718 --> 00:17:37,681
♪ <i>Who can explain it?</i> ♪

202
