248
00:27:17,135 --> 00:27:24,142
♪ <i>You may dream all alone</i> ♪

249
00:27:26,936 --> 00:27:33,401
♪ <i>Some enchanted evening</i> ♪
♪ <i>Some enchanted evening</i> ♪

250
00:27:33,484 --> 00:27:38,156
♪ <i>You may see a stranger</i> ♪

251
00:27:40,116 --> 00:27:45,329
♪ <i>You may see a stranger</i> ♪

252
00:27:45,413 --> 00:27:52,420
♪ <i>Across a crowded room...</i> ♪

253
00:27:53,671 --> 00:27:58,926
♪ <i>And somehow you know</i> ♪

254
00:27:59,010 --> 00:28:00,595
♪ <i>You know even then...</i> ♪

255
00:28:04,724 --> 00:28:07,435
♪ <i>That somewhere you'll see her...</i> ♪

256
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:11,898
♪ <i>Again and again...</i> ♪

257
00:28:16,485 --> 00:28:17,612
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Easy, pal.

258
00:28:20,364 --> 00:28:22,658
Sir, please don't make me use force.

259
00:28:25,203 --> 00:28:27,413
Oh, jeez.

260
00:28:34,128 --> 00:28:39,508
♪ <i>Some enchanted evening</i> ♪

261
00:28:39,592 --> 00:28:46,057
♪ <i>When you find your true love...</i> ♪

262
00:30:56,145 --> 00:30:57,021
Welcome.

263
00:31:03,652 --> 00:31:04,737
Oh.

264
00:31:06,781 --> 00:31:08,324
I think I know who you are.

265
00:31:08,949 --> 00:31:11,077
Everyone knows who I am.

266
00:31:14,497 --> 00:31:16,165
But do they know who they are?

267
00:31:18,417 --> 00:31:24,048
They are the product
of one of life's tricky little choices.

268
00:31:27,968 --> 00:31:29,595
So, I'm gonna offer you a choice.

269
00:31:31,639 --> 00:31:32,556
Them or her.

270
00:31:57,456 --> 00:31:59,959
- Hey. Hey, hey. Stop.
- Come on.

271
00:32:00,418 --> 00:32:01,877
-Dad.
-Trust me, please.

272
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,630
We have to-- No, no, stop!

273
00:32:07,716 --> 00:32:09,343
You are my world.

274
00:32:23,732 --> 00:32:25,234
Dad!

275
00:32:25,317 --> 00:32:27,319
Dad!
Dad!

276
00:32:27,987 --> 00:32:29,905
Stop! Stop it! Dad!

277
00:32:37,079 --> 00:32:38,497
You look like your mother.

278
00:32:43,711 --> 00:32:45,296
Where are you taking him?

279
00:32:46,338 --> 00:32:47,506
To the real world.

280
00:32:48,299 --> 00:32:49,675
You should see it sometime.

281
00:32:53,679 --> 00:32:55,473
No, wait! Stop!

282
00:33:00,644 --> 00:33:02,730
Stop! Stop!

283
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:04,815
Maybe you should do what you do best.

284
00:33:04,899 --> 00:33:07,318
-Stop!
-Run and hide.

285
00:33:50,402 --> 00:33:52,196
Hit him again!

286
00:33:55,991 --> 00:33:58,285
No, wait, wait. No, no.

287
00:33:59,119 --> 00:34:00,955
...me kicking your ass.
You like that, huh?

288
00:34:07,336 --> 00:34:08,671
Yo, let's go. Let's go.

289
00:34:21,475 --> 00:34:22,685
Hey. Wow.

290
00:34:24,770 --> 00:34:25,896
How's your nose?

291
00:34:28,524 --> 00:34:31,777
I can still smell.
It's just mostly blood.

292
00:34:33,696 --> 00:34:35,781
Flesh is weak, but Steel endures.

293
00:34:36,365 --> 00:34:37,992
I... I know.

294
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:43,080
-Come on.
-Yeah.

295
00:34:50,087 --> 00:34:53,674
♪ <i>If they ask me,
I guess I'd be denying</i> ♪

296
00:34:54,883 --> 00:34:58,304
♪ <i>That I've been unhappy all along</i> ♪

297
00:34:59,305 --> 00:35:02,516
♪ <i>But if they hurt my heart
They'd hear it crying</i> ♪

298
00:35:03,934 --> 00:35:06,645
♪ <i>"Where's my darling?
When's she coming home..."</i> ♪

299
00:35:06,729 --> 00:35:09,023
It is the duty
of the Brotherhood of Steel

300
00:35:09,106 --> 00:35:10,608
To secure the Wasteland.

301
00:35:11,275 --> 00:35:14,570
One day, as squires,
you will help knights find

302
00:35:14,653 --> 00:35:17,823
And identify pre-war tech.

303
00:35:19,116 --> 00:35:20,576
Aspirant Maximus.

304
00:35:25,998 --> 00:35:28,626
Can you identify this relic?

305
00:35:30,711 --> 00:35:31,879
It's a...

306
00:35:32,504 --> 00:35:33,339
...rotor.

307
00:35:35,549 --> 00:35:36,842
A circuit.

308
00:35:36,925 --> 00:35:40,471
The ability to defend yourself
is but one part of your training.

309
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:45,517
We are the finders and the preservers.

310
00:35:46,769 --> 00:35:49,146
Unless you know
what to find and preserve,

311
00:35:50,064 --> 00:35:53,609
You are more useful as a corpse.

312
00:36:37,403 --> 00:36:38,570
Now, look at that shit.

313
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:46,078
What kind of model is that?

314
00:36:46,161 --> 00:36:47,538
It's the T-60.

315
00:36:47,621 --> 00:36:49,873
Imagine getting to put on
one of those every day.

316
00:36:57,881 --> 00:36:59,091
Wonder why they're here.

317
00:37:02,261 --> 00:37:03,804
<i>A-17.</i>

318
00:37:06,348 --> 00:37:08,016
<i>A-28.</i>

319
00:37:10,310 --> 00:37:12,062
<i>B-11.</i>

320
00:37:13,981 --> 00:37:15,774
<i>N-24.</i>

321
00:37:33,208 --> 00:37:36,712
-Come on, got something to show you.
-Latrine duty's a two-person job.

322
00:37:37,296 --> 00:37:38,505
I said come on.

323
00:37:38,589 --> 00:37:40,632
All this shit isn't going anywhere.

324
00:38:39,733 --> 00:38:40,901
Aspirant Dane?

325
00:38:43,362 --> 00:38:46,406
-Uh... uh, this was my idea--
-You're being summoned. Come with me.

326
00:39:00,462 --> 00:39:04,633
♪ <i>Every time I look at you
I fall in love...</i> ♪

327
00:39:05,843 --> 00:39:08,637
♪ <i>All over again...</i> ♪

328
00:39:39,084 --> 00:39:40,210
What's going on?

329
00:39:41,503 --> 00:39:43,422
A bunch of us have been chosen
to get anointed.

330
00:39:44,381 --> 00:39:45,841
Hey, what's your title gonna be?

331
00:39:45,924 --> 00:39:47,259
Squire. To Knight Titus.

332
00:39:47,342 --> 00:39:49,761
And get this, we're going to the wilds.

333
00:39:49,845 --> 00:39:51,889
- Hell yeah, you are!
- Yo, D!

334
00:39:51,972 --> 00:39:54,892
D! D! D!

335
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:00,874
What happened?

336
00:41:05,170 --> 00:41:06,213
Give me that.

337
00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:39,204
♪ <i>There's a brighter side</i> ♪

338
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:44,167
♪ <i>To every dark, dark cloud</i> ♪

339
00:41:44,710 --> 00:41:50,424
♪ <i>And there's a smiling face
In every crowd...</i> ♪

340
00:41:55,178 --> 00:42:02,185
♪ <i>All your
troubles will soon fade away</i> ♪

341
00:42:03,061 --> 00:42:06,023
♪ <i>There's a brighter</i> ♪

342
00:42:06,106 --> 00:42:13,071
♪ <i>Brighter side</i> ♪

343
00:42:16,116 --> 00:42:17,159
Everyone settle.

344
00:42:20,871 --> 00:42:22,873
I have a proposal for the assembly.

345
00:42:28,754 --> 00:42:31,214
We send a search party
to the surface to find my dad.

346
00:42:31,298 --> 00:42:32,507
Go to the surface?

347
00:42:32,591 --> 00:42:35,469
We can spare four people
from farm duty for up to two weeks,

348
00:42:35,552 --> 00:42:36,636
Even with our dwindled numbers.

349
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:41,349
Sorry, Lucy, but you're talking
about opening the outer Vault door?

350
00:42:41,433 --> 00:42:43,727
Just for under a minute, okay?

351
00:42:43,810 --> 00:42:47,439
-It's just enough time to--
-Okay, I know we're brainstorming here.

352
00:42:47,522 --> 00:42:49,399
There's no bad ideas in a brainstorm.

353
00:42:49,483 --> 00:42:50,859
- Maybe a few.
- But that's not something

354
00:42:50,942 --> 00:42:54,404
That we ever do
or have ever done, never ever, ever.

355
00:42:54,488 --> 00:42:58,366
-I know. I know that, but--
-I know we're all hurting right now.

356
00:42:59,076 --> 00:43:04,122
But our first priority has to be
to maintain the security of this Vault.

357
00:43:04,206 --> 00:43:07,125
That means not opening any of our doors.

358
00:43:07,209 --> 00:43:08,168
Well said, Betty.

359
00:43:08,251 --> 00:43:11,630
Yes, thank you, Betty.
Okay, let's move on.

360
00:43:11,713 --> 00:43:13,715
They don't wanna find Dad.

361
00:43:15,550 --> 00:43:17,344
If they did, they wouldn't
get to be in charge.

362
00:44:15,694 --> 00:44:16,862
-Hey, Davey.
-Hey.

363
00:44:16,945 --> 00:44:17,779
How's your day going?

364
00:44:19,322 --> 00:44:20,657
Bad as everyone else's.

365
00:45:10,749 --> 00:45:11,833
Hold the elevator.

366
00:45:26,348 --> 00:45:29,351
Take care of Norm till I'm back, okay?

367
00:45:31,561 --> 00:45:32,562
I
can't.

368
00:45:33,730 --> 00:45:34,773
I'm going with you.

369
00:45:35,315 --> 00:45:37,400
-Chet--
-What you're doing is insane.

370
00:45:37,484 --> 00:45:39,236
You don't even know which way to go.

371
00:45:39,778 --> 00:45:42,155
It isn't like the Vault out there.
It's big.

372
00:45:47,827 --> 00:45:48,828
Chet...

373
00:45:49,746 --> 00:45:53,416
I'm not letting anyone else
get hurt on my behalf, okay?

374
00:45:59,506 --> 00:46:00,882
Oh, Lucy.

375
00:46:02,676 --> 00:46:04,719
Oh, okay. Here we go.

376
00:46:09,182 --> 00:46:10,225
Shit.

377
00:46:14,771 --> 00:46:16,731
I just tranq'd him.

378
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:19,359
I'll do the same to you
if you try to follow me.

379
00:46:20,652 --> 00:46:23,113
I'm too chicken, but thanks.

380
00:46:55,145 --> 00:46:56,354
I'm bringing him home.

381
00:47:33,058 --> 00:47:34,559
Stop! Lucy!

382
00:47:35,435 --> 00:47:36,519
Are you mad?

383
00:47:37,437 --> 00:47:40,148
Young lady, come back here right away!

384
00:47:42,067 --> 00:47:43,026
Lucy!

385
00:47:45,779 --> 00:47:47,072
Lucy, no!

386
00:47:54,079 --> 00:47:55,330
That didn't work.

387
00:49:45,315 --> 00:49:46,316
Okey dokey.

388
00:50:18,056 --> 00:50:20,600
We have given you a name.

389
00:50:23,895 --> 00:50:29,150
Food... education, a place in the world.

390
00:50:29,234 --> 00:50:30,151
So...

391
00:50:32,445 --> 00:50:36,407
We expect you to give us the truth.

392
00:50:37,283 --> 00:50:38,910
Why did you join the Brotherhood?

393
00:50:40,745 --> 00:50:42,539
To hurt the people who hurt me.

394
00:50:52,840 --> 00:50:55,552
I understand
you're a friend of Aspirant Dane.

395
00:50:56,261 --> 00:50:57,262
Yes.

396
00:50:58,721 --> 00:51:00,223
You're aware of their injury?

397
00:51:00,848 --> 00:51:02,642
-Yes.
-Do you know who did it?

398
00:51:06,854 --> 00:51:07,814
No.

399
00:51:12,652 --> 00:51:14,946
Your fellow aspirants say it was you.

400
00:51:19,325 --> 00:51:22,495
No, I... I... I wouldn't.

401
00:51:23,621 --> 00:51:24,789
Why not?

402
00:51:24,872 --> 00:51:26,874
Your friend was promoted, you were not.

403
00:51:26,958 --> 00:51:29,252
You have ambitions, don't you?

404
00:51:43,725 --> 00:51:44,684
Speak.

405
00:51:44,767 --> 00:51:47,228
I... I didn't... I didn't do it.

406
00:51:47,312 --> 00:51:48,563
I did not. I...

407
00:51:57,530 --> 00:52:00,491
I wanted it to happen.
Is that wrong?

408
00:52:06,164 --> 00:52:07,081
Yes.

409
00:52:08,416 --> 00:52:10,418
Yes.

410
00:52:12,045 --> 00:52:13,129
Violence...

411
00:52:14,047 --> 00:52:15,381
It's merely a tool.

412
00:52:16,007 --> 00:52:18,259
We use it to bring order
to the Wasteland.

413
00:52:18,343 --> 00:52:23,556
But violence against a Brother of Steel

414
00:52:24,265 --> 00:52:26,225
Is a sign of weakness.

415
00:52:30,188 --> 00:52:31,272
Are you?

416
00:52:34,692 --> 00:52:35,652
Weak?

417
00:52:40,448 --> 00:52:42,992
I... I don't wanna be. I...

418
00:53:01,803 --> 00:53:05,348
You have anything else to say
in your defense?

419
00:53:18,277 --> 00:53:19,278
I just...

420
00:53:21,989 --> 00:53:22,949
I just...

421
00:53:24,117 --> 00:53:25,660
I... I wanna thank you.

422
00:53:32,375 --> 00:53:37,672
For your guidance
and for giving me a home.

423
00:53:38,297 --> 00:53:42,427
I... I had no place in the world, so...

424
00:53:46,639 --> 00:53:49,559
If I can help the Brotherhood
make it better...

425
00:53:52,770 --> 00:53:54,814
Eden or whatever.

426
00:53:57,650 --> 00:54:02,155
Even if it means
giving my own life... I'll do it.

427
00:54:11,414 --> 00:54:14,584
And I'd be grateful to the Brotherhood
for giving my life meaning.

428
00:54:19,255 --> 00:54:20,256
Good boy.

429
00:54:25,344 --> 00:54:28,890
Then you will be
Knight Titus' new squire.

430
00:55:00,463 --> 00:55:01,631
It's not so bad.

431
00:55:03,090 --> 00:55:05,009
At least here
no one steals your rations.

432
00:55:06,803 --> 00:55:08,596
They said I'll still have a place
at the Brotherhood.

433
00:55:10,515 --> 00:55:11,974
I heard you got my spot.

434
00:55:18,064 --> 00:55:19,148
You know who did it?

435
00:55:22,026 --> 00:55:24,320
Well, I've narrowed it down
to any one of those assholes.

436
00:55:26,405 --> 00:55:29,116
-You like that? There you are.
-No! Stop it!

437
00:55:31,619 --> 00:55:33,120
They asked if it was you.

438
00:55:40,753 --> 00:55:42,296
Yeah, they asked me the same thing.

439
00:55:45,591 --> 00:55:47,718
I told them you wouldn't hurt a fly.

440
00:56:01,607 --> 00:56:03,192
Aspirant Maximus,

441
00:56:03,818 --> 00:56:07,780
It is your most sacred duty
to protect the Brotherhood.

442
00:56:08,865 --> 00:56:13,077
After which it is your most sacred duty
to protect the mission.

443
00:56:14,203 --> 00:56:17,290
After which it is your most sacred duty

444
00:56:17,373 --> 00:56:20,918
To protect your lord, Knight Titus.

445
00:56:24,088 --> 00:56:25,590
Do you accept?

446
00:56:50,656 --> 00:56:55,161
Our mission comes
from the highest clerics

447
00:56:55,995 --> 00:56:57,455
In the Commonwealth.

448
00:56:58,456 --> 00:57:03,878
It is believed that a denizen
of the Enclave

449
00:57:04,795 --> 00:57:05,713
Has escaped.

450
00:57:06,213 --> 00:57:07,298
The Enclave's real?

451
00:57:07,965 --> 00:57:14,430
And that he has with him
an object of profound potential

452
00:57:16,140 --> 00:57:20,478
To harm our nation, or to save it.

453
00:57:21,687 --> 00:57:24,607
Each knight in this legion...

454
00:57:25,816 --> 00:57:30,071
Will search a section of the wilds
for this target.

455
00:57:30,655 --> 00:57:32,031
Brothers...

456
00:57:33,199 --> 00:57:37,244
We exist for moments such as these.

457
00:57:38,412 --> 00:57:41,832
Go forth with honor!

458
00:57:43,709 --> 00:57:48,339
And may the shape of the future
be cut by your sword!

459
00:57:48,422 --> 00:57:50,049
Yeah!

460
00:57:50,132 --> 00:57:52,677
Approximation of the target
for your lord.

461
00:58:02,728 --> 00:58:04,063
You're dismissed, Aspirant.

462
00:59:46,040 --> 00:59:47,875
How do we know which grave?

463
00:59:47,958 --> 00:59:50,127
Well, Slim,
we look through the fresh ones.

464
00:59:55,007 --> 01:00:00,221
Don Pedro has our friend dug up
once a year, cuts his pieces off,

465
01:00:00,304 --> 01:00:01,931
And puts him right back in the ground.

466
01:00:10,481 --> 01:00:11,482
Bingo.

467
01:00:12,399 --> 01:00:13,275
Shit.

468
01:00:14,151 --> 01:00:16,654
You're telling me this supreme badass
we're looking for

469
01:00:16,737 --> 01:00:18,280
Is a godforsaken mutant?

470
01:00:18,364 --> 01:00:20,866
Have some respect.

471
01:00:21,659 --> 01:00:24,161
That's your prospective co-worker
you's talking about,

472
01:00:24,245 --> 01:00:26,205
And our ticket to a big pay-off.

473
01:00:26,747 --> 01:00:28,124
Don, you said you knew this guy.

474
01:00:28,207 --> 01:00:29,625
I said I knew of him.

475
01:00:31,085 --> 01:00:32,837
My pop worked with him once.

476
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:36,423
Your pop? How long has this asshole
been moldering in the ground?

477
01:00:36,507 --> 01:00:37,758
How do we know he's not feral?

478
01:00:37,842 --> 01:00:39,051
That is why

479
01:00:39,760 --> 01:00:43,055
We brought our little friend.

480
01:00:43,139 --> 01:00:46,433
A feral ghoul can't abide a chicken.

481
01:00:47,685 --> 01:00:49,728
If he goes for him, we kill him.

482
01:01:03,492 --> 01:01:05,286
Whoa, whoa.

483
01:02:26,450 --> 01:02:27,326
Ah.

484
01:02:32,915 --> 01:02:34,333
Well, well, well.

485
01:02:35,751 --> 01:02:38,712
Well, is this an Amish production
of <i>The Count of Monte Cristo,</i>

486
01:02:38,796 --> 01:02:42,800
Or just the weirdest circle jerk
I've ever been invited to?

487
01:02:52,059 --> 01:02:53,102
Welcome back.

488
01:02:54,019 --> 01:02:54,937
I'm Honcho.

489
01:02:55,020 --> 01:02:57,064
-Now, you don't even know us.
-No.

490
01:02:58,023 --> 01:02:59,525
I do not.

491
01:03:13,163 --> 01:03:14,164
Does that count?

492
01:03:15,124 --> 01:03:16,166
Should I shoot him?

493
01:03:17,167 --> 01:03:18,752
Would you shut the fuck up?

494
01:03:19,670 --> 01:03:22,589
We, uh... we got a proposition for you.

495
01:03:23,382 --> 01:03:24,717
A bounty came down.

496
01:03:25,384 --> 01:03:26,468
Well, a huge one.

497
01:03:26,552 --> 01:03:30,764
Enough to be a last score for me
and whoever's with me.

498
01:03:32,599 --> 01:03:35,102
Yeah. Now, somebody made a run...

499
01:03:37,271 --> 01:03:38,731
From the Enclave.

500
01:03:39,815 --> 01:03:42,860
Well, what makes you think
I'd give a good goddamn about that?

501
01:03:42,943 --> 01:03:46,655
It ain't where they's running from
I figured you'd be interested in.

502
01:03:46,739 --> 01:03:48,073
It's where they's running to.

503
01:03:49,616 --> 01:03:54,788
That witch Moldaver, in California.

504
01:03:56,457 --> 01:03:58,125
That's where you from, ain't it?

505
01:03:59,668 --> 01:04:01,337
Originally, I mean.

506
01:04:07,134 --> 01:04:09,720
Now, what the fuck would you know
about where I'm from?

507
01:04:12,765 --> 01:04:16,018
Well, that don't sound like gratitude,
do it, boys?

508
01:04:17,644 --> 01:04:19,772
How about we put you
right back in that hole

509
01:04:19,855 --> 01:04:23,650
So Don Pedro can have his fun with you
for the next 30 years?

510
01:04:32,951 --> 01:04:34,995
Well, I tell you what, boys,

511
01:04:35,871 --> 01:04:39,875
Whenever somebody says
they doing one last job,

512
01:04:39,958 --> 01:04:41,877
That usually means
your heart's not in it.

513
01:04:42,544 --> 01:04:44,171
Probably never was.

514
01:04:46,632 --> 01:04:48,884
Well, for me, well...

515
01:04:50,469 --> 01:04:52,596
I do this shit for the love of the game.

516
01:05:31,135 --> 01:05:32,886
You right, friend, about one thing.

517
01:05:36,056 --> 01:05:39,601
This right here was your last job.

518
01:05:40,561 --> 01:05:42,521
That paycheck wasn't quite
what you expected,

519
01:05:42,604 --> 01:05:45,482
But, well, you know what they say.

520
01:05:45,566 --> 01:05:47,484
Us cowpokes...

521
01:05:55,409 --> 01:05:57,119
...we take it as it comes.

522
01:06:17,097 --> 01:06:20,392
♪ <i>Crawl out through the fallout, baby</i> ♪

523
01:06:20,476 --> 01:06:22,686
♪ <i>When they drop that bomb</i> ♪

524
01:06:23,687 --> 01:06:26,106
♪ <i>Crawl out through the fallout</i> ♪

525
01:06:26,190 --> 01:06:29,401
♪ <i>With the greatest of aplomb</i> ♪

526
01:06:30,110 --> 01:06:33,363
♪ <i>When your white count's
getting higher</i> ♪

527
01:06:33,447 --> 01:06:35,782
♪ <i>Hurry, don't delay</i> ♪

528
01:06:35,866 --> 01:06:42,289
♪ <i>I'll hold you close and kiss
Those radiation burns away</i> ♪

529
01:06:42,998 --> 01:06:46,168
♪ <i>Crawl out through the fallout, baby</i> ♪

530
01:06:46,251 --> 01:06:48,879
♪ <i>To my loving arms</i> ♪

531
01:06:48,962 --> 01:06:55,761
♪ <i>Through the rain of strontium-90</i> ♪

532
01:06:55,844 --> 01:06:59,014
♪ <i>Think about your hero</i> ♪

533
01:06:59,097 --> 01:07:01,517
♪ <i>When you're at ground zero</i> ♪

534
01:07:01,600 --> 01:07:07,231
♪ <i>And crawl out through the fallout
Back to me</i> ♪

535
01:07:09,525 --> 01:07:15,864
♪ <i>Why don't you crawl out
Through the fallout back to me?</i> ♪

536
01:07:15,948 --> 01:07:22,204
♪ <i>Why don't you crawl out
Through the fallout back to me?</i> ♪

537
01:07:22,287 --> 01:07:28,377
♪ <i>Why don't you crawl out
Through the fallout back to...</i> ♪

538
01:07:28,460 --> 01:07:31,672
♪ <i>Me?</i> ♪

539
01:07:44,351 --> 01:07:45,310
Oh.

540
01:07:45,936 --> 01:07:46,770
Hello there.

541
01:07:47,646 --> 01:07:49,231
Now, how about we turn on some lights?

542
01:07:56,863 --> 01:07:58,448
<i>You need to go home.</i>

543
01:07:59,199 --> 01:08:01,868
Vault dwellers
are an endangered species here.

544
01:08:02,619 --> 01:08:04,246
I'm not going back without my dad.

545
01:08:07,207 --> 01:08:11,128
<i>You could have destroyed
the last vestiges of civilization.</i>

546
01:08:13,672 --> 01:08:14,840
<i>What are you looking at?</i>

547
01:08:15,299 --> 01:08:16,633
<i>A murderer in a cage.</i>

548
01:08:16,717 --> 01:08:19,177
<i>I don't know what the people
of Vault 32 were up to,</i>

549
01:08:19,761 --> 01:08:22,180
But it was anything but innocent.

550
01:08:25,851 --> 01:08:27,561
<i>What happened up here?</i>

551
01:08:29,521 --> 01:08:31,106
<i>I think everybody
wants to save the world.</i>

552
01:08:31,189 --> 01:08:32,858
<i>They just disagree on how.</i>

553
01:08:33,400 --> 01:08:34,985
<i>I wonder if anyone survived.</i>

554
01:08:36,820 --> 01:08:39,615
How long since
you first started Wastelanding?

555
01:08:39,698 --> 01:08:41,575
A long time.

556
01:08:45,996 --> 01:08:47,080
<i>What are you?</i>

557
01:08:49,291 --> 01:08:50,876
<i>Oh, I'm you, sweetie.</i>

558
01:08:51,627 --> 01:08:54,087
<i>Just give it a little time.</i>

559
01:08:55,714 --> 01:08:57,424
- Welcome!
- What the fudge?

560
01:08:58,175 --> 01:08:59,217
<i>Forget Hollywood.</i>

561
01:08:59,301 --> 01:09:00,844
<i>You're a product, I'm a product.</i>

562
01:09:02,304 --> 01:09:04,598
The end of the world is a product.

563
01:09:05,432 --> 01:09:08,226
<i>Vault-Tec is a trillion-dollar
company that owns half of everything.</i>

564
01:09:08,769 --> 01:09:10,479
<i>I guess
everything's a conspiracy, right?</i>

565
01:09:11,813 --> 01:09:13,649
<i>Unless the people
do something about it.</i>

566
01:09:17,611 --> 01:09:19,946
<i>Ain't much stays clean
up here, Vaultie.</i>

567
01:09:24,743 --> 01:09:25,577
<i>You'll see.</i>

568
01:09:39,716 --> 01:09:41,677
<i>You look out
at this wasteland...</i>

569
01:09:43,053 --> 01:09:44,680
<i>looks like chaos.</i>

570
01:09:47,641 --> 01:09:49,851
<i>But there's always somebody
behind the wheel.</i>
